National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan and Takeo Akiba, Secretary General of Japan's National Security Secretariat, held a meeting to discuss strengthening the U.S.-Japan relationship. They focused on maintaining the alliance's role in ensuring peace and security in the Indo-Pacific region and globally. The topics covered included addressing the challenge posed by China, ensuring economic and technology security, denuclearizing the Korean Peninsula, and promoting trilateral cooperation between the U.S., Japan, and South Korea. They also emphasized the importance of multilateral collaboration with ASEAN and through the Quad. Sullivan also congratulated Akiba on Japan's successful hosting of the Olympic Games.